# Phase 2: Perception Layer — Implementation Plan

## Context

Phase 1 delivered browser control: Chromium launches, navigates, interacts via CDP. gRPC server implements 5 real RPCs (session management + health), 13 stubs deferred to later phases.

Phase 2 implements the **perception layer**: the 3 RPCs currently returning `Status::unimplemented` — `get_distilled_dom`, `capture_screenshot`, `compute_diff`. These are the eyes of the nervous system. Every action produces a page diff; the agent reads distilled DOM to decide what to do next.

**Deliverable:** "Agent reads pages, sees changes, and receives screenshots — all via gRPC."

**Quality bar:** Production infrastructure — zero allocations in the hot path, walk-once DOM processing, correct tree edit distance, proper proto↔core type mapping.

---

## Architecture

```
gRPC: get_distilled_dom(DomRequest) → DistilledDom
       capture_screenshot(ScreenshotRequest) → ScreenshotResponse  
       compute_diff(DiffRequest) → DiffReport

CdpBackend::get_distilled_dom(mode)
    ├── CDP: DOM.getDocument(depth=-1) → raw JSON tree
    ├── Distiller::process(raw_dom, mode) → DistilledPage
    │   ├── Walk tree, extract elements per mode filter
    │   ├── Identify interactive elements (a, button, input, select, textarea)
    │   ├── Classify semantic blocks (nav, main, form, sidebar, footer)
    │   └── Detect distractions (ads, popups, cookie banners)
    └── serialize::to_proto(DistilledPage) → DistilledDom (in gRPC handler)

CdpBackend::capture_screenshot(format, full_page)
    └── CDP: Page.captureScreenshot → base64 → bytes
        (Already fully implemented in Phase 1)

PageDiffer::diff(before, after)
    ├── Build element identity keys: (tag, text_prefix, role, selector)
    ├── Match by identity across both trees
    ├── Compute added/removed/modified element lists
    └── Classify change: no_change, cosmetic, content_update, form_update, navigation, distraction, error_state
```

