## File-by-File Implementation

### 1. `crates/ans-distill/src/engine.rs` — DOM Distiller (rewrite from stub)

**Distiller struct** — stateless, created once:
```rust
pub struct Distiller;

impl Distiller {
    /// Process raw CDP DOM JSON into a DistilledPage.
    pub fn process(&self, raw_dom: &serde_json::Value, mode: DistillMode, 
                   url: &str, title: &str) -> DistilledPage
}
```

**Processing pipeline:**
1. Walk the CDP DOM tree recursively from `raw_dom["root"]`
2. For each node, extract: tag, text, attributes, role (from ARIA/HTML semantics)
3. Apply mode filter:
   - TextOnly: skip non-text elements, keep only text-bearing nodes and their containers
   - InputFields: keep text + interactive elements (a, button, input, select, textarea, form)
   - AllFields: keep everything, annotate with semantic metadata
4. Build three output vectors: `elements`, `interactive`, `semantic_blocks`
5. Run distraction detection on element set
6. Return DistilledPage

**Key design decisions:**
- Single-pass tree walk — no intermediate allocations
- Element identity is `tag + text[..50] + role` for diff matching
- Bounding boxes: use JS `getBoundingClientRect()` collected in batch (single Runtime.evaluate call, not one CDP call per element)
- Max elements: cap at 5000 to prevent memory issues on huge pages

### 2. `crates/ans-distill/src/semantic.rs` — Semantic Block Classification (rewrite from stub)

**Classification heuristics (no ML in v1):**
```
Navigation  ← <nav>, role="navigation", top-positioned link clusters
MainContent ← <main>, <article>, role="main", largest text block
Form        ← <form>, input/select/textarea clusters
Sidebar     ← <aside>, role="complementary", lateral position
Footer      ← <footer>, role="contentinfo", bottom position
Ad          ← class/id contains "ad", "sponsor", "banner", iframe with ad domains
CookieBanner← text contains "cookie", "gdpr", "consent"
Popup       ← position:fixed + overlay backdrop
Unknown     ← fallback
```

